!! What it does

Reusable UI component framework with composable mixins. Provides facade components (pills, vtabs) that most users consume, and a raw mixin system for advanced customization.

!! Features

* ''Facade components'' — ready-to-use: `pills` (selectable tags), `vtabs` (collapsible vertical tabs)
* ''Three-layer mixin system'' — `rrc0.*` (core/model), `rrc1.*` (behavior), consumer overrides
* ''Slot-based customization'' — `$fill` slots for custom rendering and callbacks
* ''State management'' — automatic state tiddler handling, sync to external tiddlers/fields
* ''Type dispatch'' — element types control rendering, click behavior, and visibility

!! Quick start

Two modes:

* ''Facades'' (recommended): transclude `pills` or `vtabs` with parameters + slots
* ''Raw mixins'' (advanced): import mixins directly, define `rrc0.*`/`rrc1.*` functions

Example pills usage:

```
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/pills"
  elements="Alpha Beta Gamma"
  selection="multi" />
```

Example vtabs usage:

```
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/vtabs"
  elements="[tag[Section]]"
  type-fn="[get[elem-type]]" />
```

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">Facades handle all mixin wiring internally. Most users never need to touch the `rrc0.*`/`rrc1.*` layer directly.</$fill>
</$transclude>

</$fill>
</$transclude>
